Eucalyptus leucophloia and Eucalyptus kingsmillii low open woodland over Acacia hamersleyensis (spindly form) high open shrubland over Acacia maitlandii shrubland over Triodia wiseana and Triodia longiceps hummock grassland. Eucalyptus leucophloia 4-7 m 5%; Eucalyptus kingsmillii 2-4 m < 1%; Acacia hamersleyensis (spindly form) 2-4 (5.5) m = 5-10% +; Acacia maitlandii 1-2 m (5)- 15%; Triodia wiseana 20-35 cm = 25%; Triodia longiceps 30 cm = 5%. occurrenceRemarks: 10 trees in sample, Forest Research Institute seed collection S. 10864. Tree height range 17 to 27 m, dbh range 24 to 62 cm. Density of trees variable 100-150 per hectare, for this species and for Callitris [up to] 500 stems per hectare.
habitat: Flat site; soil deep sandy with Callitris litter mixed with the surface sand, and a very thin humus layer, ph 6.5. Dry sclerophyll forest with pure stand of this species forming 100% of the cover, average height 23 m; understorey [mostly] abundant Callitris glauca but absent from part of the area; significant grassy ground cover in some areas [but also] Melaleuca sp., Melichrus sp., Bossiaea rhombifolia, Brachyloma daphnoides, Xylomelum pyriforme.
